Analyzing and Predicting Regional Sales¶

Introduction¶

The regional sales dataset includes 15 features describing product details and sales metrics. It also provides a comprehensive overview of sales channels, transactions and customer interactions.

Table of Contents¶

  1. Import Data and Packages
  2. Data Validation
  3. Data Exploration
  4. Machine Learning Methodologies

Feature Generation¶

In [1122]:
#generate new columns
df['TotalProfit']= (df['Unit Price']- df['Unit Cost']) * df['Order Quantity'] # total_profit
df['TotalSales']= df['Order Quantity']*df['Unit Price'] #TotalSales
df['ord_to_ship']= df['ShipDate'] - df['OrderDate'] # Order to shipping time
df['delivery']=  df['DeliveryDate']-df['OrderDate'] # Delivery time
df['shipping']=  df['DeliveryDate']- df['ShipDate'] # Shipping time
df['shelf_time']=df['OrderDate'] - df['ProcuredDate'] # Shelf Time

def extract_month_year(date):
    return pd.Series([date.month, date.year])

# apply function to date column
df[['month', 'year']] = df['OrderDate'].apply(extract_month_year)

list=[y_2018, y_2019, y_2020]
for x in list:
    # Plotting the time series data
    plt.figure(figsize=(15, 7))
    plt.plot(x['month'], x['TotalSales'], label='Total Sales')
    plt.title("Sales Trends Over Time")
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    plt.ylabel('Total Sales ($)')
    plt.legend()
    plt.grid(True, which='both', linestyle='--', linewidth=0.5)
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()

Immediate Insight¶

Total sales are the highest in the months of November and December. They are the lowest in late winter/early spring. The line charts show an large unpward trend in year 2018, less so in 2019. 2020 is volatile with no trend.

In [1149]:

Linear Regression¶

In [1158]:

model = LinearRegression()

# Model Performance

lg_mae = mean_absolute_error(y_test, y_pred)
lg_r2 = r2_score(y_test,y_pred)
print("Mean Squared Error:", lg_mse)
print("Mean Abs Error:", lg_mae)
print("R^2 Score:", lg_r2)
print("RMSE:", np.sqrt(lg_mse))

Predictive Model Conclusion¶

Decision Trees was best model. The model has an average error of $138.42 when predicting Unit Price based on the predictor variables. Removing redundant variables, standardizing data and hypertuning could result in more accurate predictions. To check for overfitting cross validation should be performed on the training data prior to making predictions with test data.
